energy in part of the electron

00:01:53.270 --> 00:01:57.740
is p squared over 2 times mass
of the electron, which came out

00:01:57.740 --> 00:02:05.360
to 2z squared e to the 4th
over the mass of the electron

00:02:05.360 --> 00:02:09.050
impact parameter squared
velocity squared.

00:02:09.050 --> 00:02:13.220
Then we multiplied by
the electron density

00:02:13.220 --> 00:02:18.770
in the material, which was the
number density of atoms times

00:02:18.770 --> 00:02:21.740
z, the number of
electrons per atom,

00:02:21.740 --> 00:02:25.580
times the area, the
cross-sectional area

00:02:25.580 --> 00:02:27.710
of this hollow cylindrical
shell, which came out

00:02:27.710 --> 00:02:33.740
to 2 pi b, which is the
circumference of that circle

00:02:33.740 --> 00:02:39.270
right there, times db dx.

00:02:39.270 --> 00:02:42.150
I'm just going to leave
that there for now,

00:02:42.150 --> 00:02:44.723
